<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<activity xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="act-4-3-interpret-intercepts">
    <statement>
        <p>
            For each of the stories below, write a sentence explaining what the intercept would mean in the context of the story. (Note: there's not enough information here to determine what number the intercept is!)
        </p>
        <ol marker="(a)">
            <li>
                <p>
                    Maryn is very happy. After logging many billable hours, her interior design business is finally showing a profit. 
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Since she has been pregnant, Zoe has gained the recommended amount of weight each week.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Clyde is loading bricks into his wheelbarrow. Each brick makes the total weight go up a bit.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    To make several batches of cookies, it takes a few minutes to prepare the dough, and then each batch bakes in the oven for another few minutes.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
</activity>